page.title: 01Uninhabited ground,Dalmally
page.content: The area is dominated by highground with some rough grazing. Lower slope grazing and some afforestation. Forestry for commercial use is gradually encroaching on the area. The high ground will of course remain unspoilt. Much of the area is not used by man and is rarely seen except by a few hillwalkers. Cattle graze on lower grass areas and the occasional sheep is to be found on higher slopes. Small streams crisscross the area providing water for nearby farms although human habitation is not present within the block.
